Read in Data

#set your data directory
data_dir <- "~/brca-new/own data/"

#list all TSV files that match the naming pattern
tsv_files <- list.files(path = data_dir, pattern = "^cnv_exon_overlaps_.*\\.tsv$", full.names = TRUE)

#create a named list of data frames, using file identifiers (e.g., B1.43) as names
overlap_data_list <- setNames(
  lapply(tsv_files, read_tsv),
  nm = gsub("^cnv_exon_overlaps_|\\.tsv$", "", basename(tsv_files))
)

#combine specific data frames into one
overlap_df <- bind_rows(
  overlap_data_list$B1.43,
  overlap_data_list$B1.49,
  overlap_data_list$B1.6410,
  overlap_data_list$B1.6537,
  overlap_data_list$B1.6548,
  overlap_data_list$B1.6550,
  overlap_data_list$B2.6532,
  overlap_data_list$B2.18,
  overlap_data_list$B2.25,
  overlap_data_list$B2.16,
  overlap_data_list$B2.21,
  overlap_data_list$B2.23,
  overlap_data_list$WT.6,
  overlap_data_list$WT.62,
  overlap_data_list$WT.6752
)


#organize b2 samples by tissue type (show tumor progression ALH-LCIS-DCIS)
overlap_df$sample <- factor(overlap_df$sample, levels = c(
  "B1.43", "B1.49", "B1.6410", "B1.6537", "B1.6548", "B1.6550",
  "B2.6532","B2.18", "B2.25", "B2.16", "B2.21", "B2.23",
  "WT.6", "WT.62", "WT.6752"))

#reorder tissue levels
overlap_df <- overlap_df %>%
  mutate(tissue = factor(tissue, levels = c("benign", "ALH", "LCIS", "DCIS")))

Plots

BRCA2

BRCA2 Germline Cells with B2 LOH + TP53 Som-Mut

  • There are 18 cells that have both a CND covering all of BRCA2 and TP53 in BRCA2 germline epithelial breast cells.
# Filter BRCA1 and TP53 Mut separately
brca2_loh_cells <- overlap_df %>%
  filter(genotype == "B2", gene == "BRCA2", state < 2) %>%
  pull(cell_id) %>%
  unique()

tp53_loh_cells <- overlap_df %>%
  filter(genotype == "B2", gene == "TP53", state < 2) %>%
  pull(cell_id) %>%
  unique()

# Find intersection
som_loh_cells <- intersect(brca2_loh_cells, tp53_loh_cells)
length(som_loh_cells)
## [1] 18

B2-TP53: Violin Plot of Bases Deleted for BRCA2 in BRCA2 Germline Cells

#filter for B1
brca2 <- overlap_df %>% filter(genotype == "B2", gene == "BRCA2")

#ID cells with LOH in BRCA1
loh.brca2 <- brca2 %>%
  filter(state < 2) %>%
  group_by(cell_id) %>%
  mutate(loh = TRUE, 
         del = exon_end - exon_start,
         tp53 = cell_id %in% som_loh_cells)

#merge back into main dataframe to label cells
het.brca2 <- brca2 %>%
  filter(state >= 2) %>%
  group_by(cell_id) %>%
  mutate(loh = FALSE,
         #heterozygosity = "HET",
         del = 0)

#combine dfs
brca2 <- rbind(loh.brca2, het.brca2)  %>%
  mutate(
    loh_status = case_when(
      loh == TRUE & tp53 == TRUE ~ "LOH+TP53",
      loh == TRUE & tp53 == FALSE ~ "LOH_only",
      loh == FALSE ~ "HET"
    )
  )

#plot
ggplot(brca2, aes(x = sample, y = del, fill = loh_status)) +
  geom_violin(position = "identity", alpha = 0.5, color = NA) +
  #colouring
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(
      "HET" = "lightgrey",
      "LOH_only" = "red",
      "LOH+TP53" = "blue"
    )
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      "HET" = "grey20",
      "LOH_only" = "darkred",
      "LOH+TP53" = "darkblue"
    )
  ) +
  #point shape (chemo vs non chemo)
  geom_point(
    aes(shape = chemo),     #shapes by chemo
    position = position_jitter(width = 0.2, height = 0.1),
    size = 2,
    color = "black",                #black outline
    stroke = 0.5                    #outline thickness
  ) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(21, 24)) +  #21 = circle, 24 = triangle
  #theme
  theme_minimal(base_size = 15) +
  #figure adjustments
  theme(legend.position = "right",
        panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA, color = "black", linewidth = 1.5),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = "grey90", color = "black", size = 1.5),
        panel.spacing = unit(1, "lines"),
        #axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 48, hjust = 1, size = 15),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10),
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
        axis.title.x=element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(face = "bold")) +
  #facet  
  facet_grid(. ~ tissue, scales = "free", space = "free") + 
  labs(
    x = NULL,
    y = "Bases Deleted (BRCA2)",
    fill = "BRCA2 LOH",
    color = "BRCA2 LOH",
    title = "CNDs of BRCA2 in BRCA2 Germline Cells"
  )
